Class KeyBindings

java.lang.Object
com.example.demo.utils.KeyBindings
public class KeyBindings extends Object
A singleton class for managing key bindings used in the application. This class provides a centralized way to manage key mappings for up, down, left, and right actions.

  • Constructor Details

    • KeyBindings

      private KeyBindings()
      Private constructor to prevent direct instantiation. Initializes the key bindings to default values:
      • Up key: KeyCode.UP
      • Down key: KeyCode.DOWN
      • Left key: KeyCode.LEFT
      • Right key: KeyCode.RIGHT
